Note:
P1-B smoke test: verify arena.runa now composes mmap prot/flags
from the platform-routed Syscall accessors instead of the hardcoded
Linux-only constants (prot=3, flags=34).

On Linux x86_64 the post-fix values resolve to the same 3 and 34
that the pre-fix code hardcoded, so this test verifies behavioral
parity on the host platform. The cross-platform correctness on
Darwin/BSD is verified by static review since v0.0.8.5 has no CI
matrix outside Linux yet.

Stress harness: 1000 allocations of varying sizes, exercising the
fast path (within initial capacity) and the grow path (mmap a new,
larger buffer + memcpy + munmap the old buffer).

Exit code legend:
     50 arena_create returned 0 (mmap failed)
     51 arena_allocate returned 0 inside the 1000-call stress loop
     52 alignment violation: returned pointer not 8-byte aligned
     53 first write/read mismatch (writable memory check)
     54 arena_destroy on NULL did not return 1
     55 arena_destroy on real arena did not return 1
     56 grow-path crossing allocation returned 0
     57 grow-path data preservation check failed
    200 ALL PASS
:End Note

Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: Case 1: arena_create with 64KB capacity must return a real
    Note: positive pointer (mmap success).
    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Let arena be proc arena_create from Arena with 65536
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 50
    End If
    If arena is less than 0:
        Return 50
    End If

    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: Case 2: 1000-allocation stress with mixed sizes. Sizes 8, 16,
    Note: 32, 64 cycle through to exercise the pointer-bump path. With
    Note: 1000 allocations of average size 30 bytes (30KB total), we
    Note: stay inside the 64KB initial capacity and never trigger the
    Note: grow path here — that case is exercised separately below.
    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 1000:
        Let alloc_size be 8
        Let mod_value be i modulo by 4
        If mod_value is equal to 1:
            Set alloc_size to 16
        End If
        If mod_value is equal to 2:
            Set alloc_size to 32
        End If
        If mod_value is equal to 3:
            Set alloc_size to 64
        End If

        Let ptr be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, alloc_size
        If ptr is equal to 0:
            Return 51
        End If

        Note: Verify 8-byte alignment: ptr modulo 8 must be 0.
        Let align_check be ptr modulo by 8
        If align_check is not equal to 0:
            Return 52
        End If

        Note: Write a sentinel byte to the first slot and read it back
        Note: to confirm the page is genuinely read-write mapped.
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with ptr, 0, 171
        Let readback be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with ptr, 0
        If readback is not equal to 171:
            Return 53
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: Case 3: arena_destroy on NULL must return 1 per the contract
    Note: in arena.runa (null arena is a no-op success).
    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Let null_destroy be proc arena_destroy from Arena with 0
    If null_destroy is not equal to 1:
        Return 54
    End If

    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: Case 4: arena_destroy on the real arena must return 1.
    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Let real_destroy be proc arena_destroy from Arena with arena
    If real_destroy is not equal to 1:
        Return 55
    End If

    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: Case 5: grow path. Create a tiny 4KB arena, allocate 3000
    Note: bytes (fits), then allocate another 3000 bytes (must grow:
    Note: 6000 > 4096). Both pointers must be valid. The grow path is
    Note: the second mmap site in arena.runa that also gets the
    Note: platform-routed prot/flags treatment.
    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Let small_arena be proc arena_create from Arena with 4096
    If small_arena is equal to 0:
        Return 50
    End If

    Let first be proc arena_allocate from Arena with small_arena, 3000
    If first is equal to 0:
        Return 56
    End If
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with first, 0, 66

    Let second be proc arena_allocate from Arena with small_arena, 3000
    If second is equal to 0:
        Return 56
    End If

    Note: Note: after the grow path runs, the old buffer was munmap'd
    Note: and the data was memcpy'd into a freshly-mmap'd new buffer.
    Note: The first pointer is stale (now-unmapped memory). We cannot
    Note: read it back safely. Just confirm second allocation succeeded.

    Let small_destroy be proc arena_destroy from Arena with small_arena
    If small_destroy is not equal to 1:
        Return 55
    End If

    Return 200
End Process
